body:
Hi, upon compiling the following code:

```
module shift_reg
  #(
    parameter WIDTH = 1,
    parameter DEPTH = 2
    )
   (
    input 	       i_clk,
    input 	       i_rstb,
    input [WIDTH-1:0]  i_data,
    output [WIDTH-1:0] o_data
    );

   reg [WIDTH-1:0]     sreg [DEPTH-1:0];   
   integer 	       i;   

   assign o_data = sreg[DEPTH-1];
   
   always @(posedge i_clk or negedge i_rstb)
     if (!i_rstb)
       for (i = 0; i<DEPTH; i++)
	 sreg[i] <= {WIDTH{1'b0}};   
     else
       begin
	  sreg[0] <= #0.2 i_data;
	  sreg[DEPTH-1:1] <= #0.2 sreg[DEPTH-2:0];	  
       end

endmodule // shift_reg
```

Using the command:
`iverilog -g2005-sv -o sr shift_reg.v`

I get the following error:
```
shift_reg.v:27: error: cannot perform a part select on array sreg.
1 error(s) during elaboration.
```

The line being referred to in the error message is:
`  sreg[DEPTH-1:1] <= #0.2 sreg[DEPTH-2:0];	`

